# Git sync after changes

When you finish a task that modifies files in this repository, push to GitHub:

1. Run `git status`.
2. If there are unstaged or uncommitted changes: `git add -A`, then `git commit -m "<short descriptive message>"`, then `git push`.

A Cursor **stop** hook may also run `git add` / `commit` / `push` when an agent run ends. If you already committed and pushed, the hook will typically see a clean tree and do nothing. Prefer clear commit messages when you run git yourself (the hook uses a generic timestamp message).
